  were encountered, thus [None] means [is_valid = true].

- Edit the test file to be in sync with the code quoted in the doc,
  also changed a date which was out of sync (unimportant).

commit.message: Release 2.15.0

[atddiff] Offer '--no-locations' option (#382)

* Add new option '--no-locations' for omitting file/line/column from reports

* Add a location-independent hash to each finding and use it for sorting
results with --no-locations.

* Update changelog

* Change the hash function parameters to ensure it will use all the data

* Explain the finding hashes in the help for `--no-locations`

* Mark `atddiff --no-locations` as experimental because it's a little
weird and may not be the best solution for tracking atddiff findings
over time.

* Announce the breaking change in the JSON output of atddiff

---------

Co-authored-by: Martin Jambon <martin@semgrep.com>
